main event: An unidentified flying object was reported in Reno, Nevada, observed over several hours with varied characteristics.
interesting points: The sighting included objects that were described to be like the moon and exhibited unusual motion., One object was observed for 4 hours while the other was considered a meteor passing quickly., The objects were observed moving west and had no sound associated with them., Observers considered natural and man-made explanations for the sightings., Multiple observations noted differences in color and behavior of the objects, with one brighter than Venus.
witness description: Civilian observers with varying evaluations of the objects.
